FAQs about Study in Hungary
1. What are the entry requirements for studying medicine in Hungary?
Entry requirements typically include a high school diploma or equivalent qualification with strong grades in science subjects like Biology, Chemistry, and Physics. Proficiency in English or Hungarian may also be required, depending on the language of instruction.

2. Are there any entrance exams for medical programs in Hungary?
Some universities may require applicants to pass an entrance exam or undergo an interview as part of the admission process. It's essential to check the specific requirements of each university and program.

3. Can international students apply to study medicine in Hungary?
Yes, international students are welcome to apply to medical programs in Hungary. Many universities offer programs taught in English, making it accessible to students from around the world.

4. What is the duration of medical programs in Hungary?
The duration of medical programs in Hungary varies depending on the university and program. Typically, undergraduate medical degrees take around six years to complete, including both theoretical studies and clinical training.

